BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260315
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260316
SUMMARY:🌿 Bee Balm Division + Raspberry Transplant (half day)
DESCRIPTION:BEE BALM DIVISION:\n1. Find overgrown clumps (square stems, runners)\n2. Water night before\n3. Spade through root mass — divide 3-5 sections each\n4. Toss woody centers\n5. Plant: 2-3 clumps → Wayward Meadow (18-24" apart), 1-2 → Alchemist's Pond (buried container), extras → pots\n6. Water deeply, mulch\n\nRASPBERRY TRANSPLANT:\n• Dig 4 Red Latham canes, keep root balls intact\n• Mark row 3-4 ft south of blueberries\n• Mix planting soil + compost + peat moss\n• 4 holes, 4-5 ft apart, 18" wide x 12" deep\n• Set trellis posts, run wire at 2 ft and 4 ft\n• Sink root barrier 12" on south edge\n• Mulch 4-6" (keep 6" from stems)\n• Scatter chive seeds along edges\n• Water deeply\n\nIF TIME: sow turnips (window Mar 8–30)
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT0H
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Bee Balm + Raspberry day!
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260316
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260317
SUMMARY:🌱 Indoor Starts + Bed Prep (full day)
DESCRIPTION:INDOOR STARTS:\n• Pumpkins (Jack O'Lantern, Small Sugar) — large pots. Window: Mar 16–30\n• Zucchini (Summer Melody Blend) — window closes Mar 23\n• Squash (Winter Vegetable Spaghetti) — window closes Mar 23\n\nBED PREP — BLOOMVEIL:\n• Turn soil, add compost, edge with bricks/stones\n• Mark zones with stakes or flags\n\nBED PREP — WILDWOOD:\n• Outline veggie bed boundaries with twine/chalk/sticks\n• Move bricks to edge beds or spiral
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT0H
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Indoor starts + bed prep day
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT

