BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261101
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261102
SUMMARY:❄️ Average First Fall Frost
DESCRIPTION:Average first frost for Fuquay-Varina/Apex area: November 1.\n\n• Cover any remaining tender crops or harvest now\n• Dig dahlia tubers if you chose that method (after foliage blackens)\n• Garlic planting window — check soil temp (plant when soil is 60°F at 4" depth)\n• Mulch everything\n• Garden is winding down — good work this year!
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT0H
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:First frost expected
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260309
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260310
SUMMARY:🌶️ Start Tomatoes + Peppers Indoors (late but doable!)
DESCRIPTION:Start seeds indoors TODAY:\n\nTOMATOES (6-8 weeks to transplant size):\n• Use seed starting mix in small pots/cells\n• 1/4" deep, keep moist\n• 70-80°F for germination (heat mat helps)\n• Transplant outdoors late April/early May\n\nBELL PEPPERS (8-10 weeks to transplant):\n• Same as tomatoes but slower to germinate\n• Keep extra warm (80°F ideal)\n• Be patient — peppers can take 2-3 weeks to sprout\n\nYou're ~2-3 weeks behind schedule but Zone 7b's long season gives you plenty of buffer. Worst case: buy nursery backup transplants in April.
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT0H
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Start tomato + pepper seeds indoors!
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260410
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260411
SUMMARY:🌶️ Backup Plan — Buy tomato + pepper transplants?
DESCRIPTION:Check your indoor tomato and pepper starts:\n• Are they at least 6" tall with true leaves?\n• Sturdy stems?\n\nIF YES: Great! Start hardening off this week, transplant Apr 15-20.\n\nIF NO (leggy, weak, or didn't germinate): Head to a nursery this weekend.\nGood local options: Logan's, Garden Supply Co, big box stores.\n\nLook for:\n• Tomato varieties you want (check your seed list)\n• Bell pepper starts\n• Stocky plants with dark green leaves, no flowers yet
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT0H
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Check tomato/pepper starts — need nursery backup?
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260309
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260310
SUMMARY:🌿 Start Medicinal Herbs Indoors — Phase 1
DESCRIPTION:Start these from the SeedTherapy kit indoors alongside your tomatoes/peppers:\n\n• ASHWAGANDHA (30 seeds) — needs long warm season\n  Barely cover, keep 70-75°F, 14-21 day germination\n\n• HOLY BASIL / TULSI (100 seeds) — start like regular basil\n  1/4" deep, 70-75°F, 7-14 days\n\n• CAYENNE PEPPER (30 seeds) — start with your other peppers\n  1/4" deep, 80°F ideal, 14-21 days\n\n• TOOTHACHE PLANT (50 seeds) — frost tender\n  Surface sow, press in, don't cover. 70-75°F, 10-14 days\n\nAll 4 go on the same heat mat / windowsill as your tomatoes and peppers.
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT0H
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Start medicinal herb seeds indoors!
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260415
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260416
SUMMARY:🌿 Medicinal Herbs Phase 2 — Direct Sow Motherwort + More
DESCRIPTION:Direct sow these in The Gloam / apothecary garden:\n\n• MOTHERWORT — press onto soil surface, DO NOT COVER (needs light). Keep moist. For your tincture!\n• FEVERFEW — surface sow, don't cover\n• FENUGREEK — 1/4" deep, easy\n• CHAMOMILE (extra from kit) — scatter on prepared soil\n• CALENDULA (extra from kit) — 1/4" deep\n\nAlso transplant Phase 1 indoor starts (ashwagandha, tulsi, cayenne, toothache plant) — harden off first!
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT0H
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Sow motherwort + Phase 2 medicinals!
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260501
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260502
SUMMARY:🌿 Medicinal Herbs Phase 3 — Main Apothecary Planting
DESCRIPTION:Direct sow the bigger medicinals in The Gloam:\n\nTALL BACKS:\n• Mullein — scatter on bare/disturbed soil, loves poor soil\n• Marshmallow — 1/4" deep\n• Angelica — direct sow, give part shade\n• Burdock — direct sow (taproot, don't transplant)\n• Hollyhock — 1/4" deep\n• Chicory — scatter, press in\n\nWORKING MIDDLE:\n• St. John's Wort — surface sow, needs light\n• Skullcap — surface sow\n• Horehound — 1/4" deep\n\nCONTAINED (buried pots!):\n• Mugwort — buried 5-gal pot ONLY\n• Stinging Nettle — buried pot, back corner, WEAR GLOVES\n• Wild Licorice — buried 3-gal pot\n\nAlso: Plant elderberry seeds in pots (or buy a live plant for faster fruit)
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT0H
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Main apothecary garden planting day!
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260701
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260702
SUMMARY:🌿 Motherwort Harvest Check — Tincture Time?
DESCRIPTION:If your motherwort is flowering (likely year 2, but check anyway):\n\n• Harvest when in FULL BLOOM\n• Cut top 1/3 of flowering stems\n• Morning after dew, before peak heat\n• Don't take more than 1/3 of any plant\n\nTINCTURE:\n1. Chop coarsely, fill mason jar 2/3 full\n2. Cover completely with 100 proof vodka\n3. Stir out air bubbles\n4. Cap, label with date\n5. Shake daily for 6 weeks\n6. Strain → amber dropper bottles\n\nAlso check: St. John's Wort flowers (solar oil), chamomile (tea harvest), calendula (salve harvest)
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT0H
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Check motherwort — ready for tincture?
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260915
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260916
SUMMARY:🌿 Fall Root Harvest — Apothecary Garden
DESCRIPTION:DIG ROOTS (medicine is in the roots for these):\n\n• ASHWAGANDHA — dig entire root, wash, chop, dry or tincture\n• BURDOCK — dig taproot end of year 1 (or wait to spring year 2)\n• VALERIAN — dig roots fall of year 2+ (smells awful, works amazing)\n• ECHINACEA — dig some roots year 3+ (leave most to keep growing)\n\nALSO:\n• Collect elderberries if fruiting (cook before eating — never raw!)\n• Dry remaining herb harvests for winter tea blends\n• Collect seeds from motherwort, feverfew, mullein for next year\n• Pull annual medicinals (tulsi, ashwagandha, toothache plant, fenugreek)
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT0H
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Fall root harvest — apothecary garden
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT

END:VCALENDAR
